705416f-b.text:
(1)
Leonard Street, east side, south from Ten Eyek Street, showing the cleared area, formerly occupied by tenements, where the Williamsburg Houses--a low rent governmental housing center, will be erected. In the background is the steeple of the Most Holy Trinity Roman Catholic Church, on Montrose Avenue.
October 27, 1936
P. L. Sperr
(2). (3)
Across the same area, in a more easterly direction, showing a new school under construction.
VUew 2: August 10, 1936
View 3: October 27, 1936
P. L. Sperr
